args:
Yachiyo demands the truth from Saiga about the
Mukuroshu man's claims. When he remains
silent, she challenges him to a duel with the
following terms: If she wins, he must obey a
single order from her. But if he wins, she will
hand over the scroll.
Okay, I think that pretty much wraps up the\nones that were around here, yeah?\nAll of the others are—
Is what the Mukuroshu said true?!\nDid you kill Grandpappy?!
Why?! What's your game here, and what's\nthis ＂goal＂ that two-bit boneman was\ntalking about?! ...ANSWER ME!
I will not speak of it to you.

I am not the man I was; I strayed from
the path of justice to achieve my aim.
There is no point in our bandying words
about it now.
I do not need allies to get things done. \nConsequently, I ask that you give me the\nscroll so I might accomplish my goal.
You must think I'm a real maroon!
Easy, you two! We've got enough people\ntrying to claw out our throats without us\ndoing it for 'em!
Saiga, I challenge you to a duel!
Yachiyo, no! You can't be serious!
Oh, I'm serious as a heart attack! If this\ndope wants to play dumb about all this,\nI'm gonna make him sing like a canary!
What fool nonsense are you on about?\nWhat could I possibly have to gain from\naccepting a duel with you?
If you win, I'll fork over the scroll.

BUT! If I come out in the money, you have
to accept one command from me—and if
I tell you to answer a question, it has to
be the complete truth with no flimflam.
I'm not sure it's a good idea to wager\nyour grandfather's scroll like this.
If I don't, he won't tell me boo.
Plus, if what the Mukuroshu guy said is\ntrue, this duel was always gonna happen.
I've gone round and round with hundreds\nof warriors over the course of my journey.
It was my grandpappy's greatest wish,\nbut he got iced before he could see it\nthrough to the end.
And now, the man who rubbed him out\nis standing in front of me clear as day,\nso we're gonna duel one way or the other!
Very well. I accept your challenge\nand your conditions.
However, I will specify the time and place\nfor our duel to occur.
Fine by me. We could do it right now as\nfar as I'm concerned. I'm always ready to\ntussle.

Ah, yes... ＂Act ever as if you are on the
battlefield, that you can face a fight no
matter when it arrives before you.＂
One of our master's teachings.
In that case, as soon as I am prepared,\nI will pen a missive upon which you will\nfind the location and date of our duel.
And with that, I am now away!
We'd better skedaddle back to the Halidom\nso I can get ready.
Heh heh... I could make good use of this...
Early the following morning\nThe Halidom, Yachiyo's Room
There's a hawk in the castle...and hot\ndamn! It's got a note around its leg.
Yeah, I got what I need here, birdie.\nNow fly on home to my brother-in-law.
Get ready, Saiga, 'cause I'm gonna give\nyou a licking you won't ever forget!
